&gt; 1.) I never got a copy of the will.  She was a California resident.
&gt; How can I get a copy of the will?
">

Was there a probate?  If so, a copy will be in the court's file.  If
not, the custodian of the will was required to deposit it with the
county clerk within 30 days after your mother died.  That may not have
happened, but it's what is supposed to happen.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; 2.) Once I get a copy of the will, how can I assess whether it was
&gt; properly executed and be certain I was fairly included?
">

If there was a probate, it's probably too late for you to do anything
about it at this point.

